  "body": "Instead of just per-project config files.\r\n\r\nWe should add logic so that, if it doesn't exist, Truffle creates a directory somewhere in the user's home directory (e.g. `~/.config/truffle` on Linux/Mac), to enable future configuration options.\r\n\r\nWe likely want to find a widely-used library for this purpose (there's probably _something_ on NPM that can do this in an OS-independent manner).\r\n\r\nFor purposes of this issue, we don't need to add any configuration options, but this work should involve the logic necessary to read and write to this config.\r\n\r\nThis might involve the creation of a `truffle config` command, although requirements would need to be scoped out.",
